# Code Compass — Cursor Rules

## Tooling vs AI (Critical Separation)

Never use LLMs for deterministic tasks. Use native tools instead.

| Task | Tool | AI |
|------|------|-----|
| Formatting | Prettier, Black, gofmt, clang-format, rustfmt | ❌ |
| Linting | ESLint, Ruff (sandbox) | ❌ |
| Validation | Zod | ❌ |
| Diffs | Monaco | ❌ |
| File ops | Native FS | ❌ |
| Planning | — | ✓ |
| Reasoning | — | ✓ |
| Refactoring | — | ✓ |

- Use `lib/formatters` and `prepareEditContent()` for edit content; never ask LLM to format.
- Use Zod for schema validation; never ask LLM to validate.
- Use `parseJSONRobust` for LLM output parsing.
